ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "PatriotDescendant", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "www.bizpacreview.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASG9YEK1Q.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://www.bizpacreview.com/2026/03/07/us-executes-targeted-strike-against-suspected-narco-terrorist-network-in-ecuador-1626051/", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "US executes targeted strike against suspected narco-terrorist network in Ecuador", "last_comment_created": 1772896479506, "content": "", "score_down": 1, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 1, "score_up": 56, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"description": "The U.S. military executed a targeted joint strike Friday against a \u201cnarco-terrorist\u201d drug-smuggling facility in Ecuador. The strike was conducted at the request of the Ecuadorean government [\u2026]", "large_image": "7taLlTvuO26B9lhz.png", "title": "US executes targeted strike against suspected narco-terrorist network in Ecuador"}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASG9YEK1P", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 55, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8472397, "raw_content": "Look, Persia's history dates way back further than '79 obviously.  But '79 marked the rise of the fundamentalists and hardline Mullah rule.\n\nPrior to '79 Iran was a progressive nation by middle eastern standards.  It had an educated populace and people on the street looked almost westernized.  Many Americans worked in Iran on temporary basis and it was an exploding economy.\n\nThere were many Iranians who escaped in 79 and live in exile in other nations.  There is a significant contingent here.  \n\nIran has the makings of a \"constitutional monarchy in exile\".  There may be a shot at bringing in a new government.  We have heard that Iran's population hates the Mullahs and there are some signs since the war began that is true.\n\nThere are still Iranians around that remember pre-1979.  The Islamic revolution is about 46 years old.  So, it's not like it's been this way for 200 years.\n\nWho knows the odds of success of a new more western type of government.  But the future w/ mullahs controlling nukes, was in many circles thought to be untenable.\n\nThere is a limit to what can be forced on the Iranian population.  It is going to have to step up and self-rule.  \n\nAs for America's position 1979 was never properly dealt with.  Had Jimmy Carter not be the weak pathetic president he was, perhaps the world would not be in this position.\n\nIt appears that DJT is attempting resolve many of the world's lingering issues.\n\n", "author": "dataonly", "created": 1772895953660, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Taylor3006", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Iran has Been the Constant Issue in the Middle East and Worldwide Since 1979", "last_comment_created": 1772911527732, "content": "<p>Look, Persia's history dates way back further than '79 obviously.  But '79 marked the rise of the fundamentalists and hardline Mullah rule.</p>\n<p>Prior to '79 Iran was a progressive nation by middle eastern standards.  It had an educated populace and people on the street looked almost westernized.  Many Americans worked in Iran on temporary basis and it was an exploding economy.</p>\n<p>There were many Iranians who escaped in 79 and live in exile in other nations.  There is a significant contingent here.</p>\n<p>Iran has the makings of a &quot;constitutional monarchy in exile&quot;.  There may be a shot at bringing in a new government.  We have heard that Iran's population hates the Mullahs and there are some signs since the war began that is true.</p>\n<p>There are still Iranians around that remember pre-1979.  The Islamic revolution is about 46 years old.  So, it's not like it's been this way for 200 years.</p>\n<p>Who knows the odds of success of a new more western type of government.  But the future w/ mullahs controlling nukes, was in many circles thought to be untenable.</p>\n<p>There is a limit to what can be forced on the Iranian population.  It is going to have to step up and self-rule.</p>\n<p>As for America's position 1979 was never properly dealt with.  Had Jimmy Carter not be the weak pathetic president he was, perhaps the world would not be in this position.</p>\n<p>It appears that DJT is attempting resolve many of the world's lingering issues.</p>\n", "score_down": 4, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 11, "score_up": 59, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASG9YEJgn", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 61, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8472349, "raw_content": "", "author": "wst4", "created": 1772893409213, "profile_picture": "q5m3F9Z03pfi", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "someguy7738", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "media.scored.co", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASG9YEJgn.png", "removal_source": "", "l